			<div id="post-6" class="post-6 page type-page status-publish hentry">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/engage/case-studies/" title="Permalink to Case Studies" rel="bookmark">Case Studies</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/engage/case-studies/" title="8:52 pm" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">July 17, 2013</span></a> <span class="meta-sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/engage/author/klindsay/" title="View all posts by Katharine Lindsay">Katharine Lindsay</a></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p>We have compiled a number of case studies of Oxford people using digital technologies to support public engagement and impact. These can be found on our separate <a href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/ltg-casestudies/" title="LTG case studies" target="_blank">case studies website</a>.</p>
<p style="padding: 2px 6px 4px 6px;color: #555555;background-color: #eeeeee;border: #dddddd 2px solid"><a title="A Digital Dodo? Building a Social Media Presence for the Museum of Natural History" href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/ltg-casestudies/2013/09/13/a-digital-dodo-building-a-social-media-presence-for-the-museum-of-natural-history/">A Digital Dodo? Building a Social Media Presence for the Museum of Natural History</a> Scott Billings, Oxford University Natural History Museum</p>
<p style="padding: 2px 6px 4px 6px;color: #555555;background-color: #eeeeee;border: #dddddd 2px solid"><a title="OxTweet: A Virtual Taste of Student Life" href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/ltg-casestudies/2013/09/13/oxtweet-a-virtual-taste-of-student-life/">OxTweet: A Virtual Taste of Student Life</a> Jamie Miles &amp; Simon Clark, undergraduate students reading PPE at Magdalen, and Physics at St Peter’s.</p>
<p style="padding: 2px 6px 4px 6px;color: #555555;background-color: #eeeeee;border: #dddddd 2px solid"><a title="Blogging the truth about research" href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/ltg-casestudies/2013/03/07/blogging-the-truth-about-research/" target="_blank">Blogging the truth about research</a> Peter Gill, Centre for Evidence-based Medical Research at the Department of Primary Care.</p>
<p style="padding: 2px 6px 4px 6px;color: #555555;background-color: #eeeeee;border: #dddddd 2px solid"><a title="Rethinking Impact: Social Media" href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/ltg-casestudies/2012/12/12/rethinking-impact-social-media/" target="_blank">Rethinking Impact: Social Media</a> Nando Sigona, Oxford University Refugee Studies Centre.</p>
<p style="padding: 2px 6px 4px 6px;color: #555555;background-color: #eeeeee;border: #dddddd 2px solid"><a href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/ltg-casestudies/2012/12/09/digital-story-telling-the-arras95-live-tweeting-project/" target="_blank">Digital story-telling: the @Arras95 live-tweeting project</a> World War I: Continuations and Beginnings, IT Services</p>
<p style="padding: 2px 6px 4px 6px;color: #555555;background-color: #eeeeee;border: #dddddd 2px solid"><a title="Permalink to Improving Public Understanding of Science: Social Media and Digital Technologies" href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/ltg-casestudies/2012/10/20/improving-public-understanding-of-science-social-media-and-digital-technologies/">Improving Public Understanding of Science: Social Media and Digital Technologies </a>Marcus du Sautoy, Simonyi Professor for the Public Understanding of Science and a Professor of Mathematics</p>
<p style="padding: 2px 6px 4px 6px;color: #555555;background-color: #eeeeee;border: #dddddd 2px solid"><a title="Permalink to Open Educational Resources: A contributor’s case-study" href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/ltg-casestudies/2012/08/23/open-educational-resources-a-contributors-case-study/">Open Educational Resources: A contributor’s case-study </a>Marianne Talbot, lecturer in philosophy at the Department for Continuing Education</p>
<p style="padding: 2px 6px 4px 6px;color: #555555;background-color: #eeeeee;border: #dddddd 2px solid"><a title="UNIQ Summer School" href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/ltg-casestudies/2012/08/22/social-media-engagement-uniq-summer-school-and-facebook/">Social media engagement: UNIQ Summer School and Facebook </a>Widening Access, University of Oxford</p>
<p style="padding: 2px 6px 4px 6px;color: #555555;background-color: #eeeeee;border: #dddddd 2px solid"><a title="RunCoCo" href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/ltg-casestudies/2012/08/13/crowd-sourcing-for-engagement-runcoco/" rel="xh:bookmark xh:bookmark xh:bookmark xh:bookmark bookmark">Crowdsourcing for Engagement: RunCoCo </a>Alun Edwards, IT Services</p>
<p style="padding: 2px 6px 4px 6px;color: #555555;background-color: #eeeeee;border: #dddddd 2px solid"><a title="Online scholarly engagement: Blogging and tweeting" href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/ltg-casestudies/2012/08/03/online-scholarly-engagement-blogging-and-tweeting/"> Online scholarly engagement: Blogging and tweeting</a>Prof Elizabeth Eva Leach, Tutorial Fellow in Music at St Hugh’s College and Lecturer in Music at Exeter College</p>
<p style="padding: 2px 6px 4px 6px;color: #555555;background-color: #eeeeee;border: #dddddd 2px solid"><a title="Blogging to Engage: Politics in Spires" href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/ltg-casestudies/2012/07/09/blogging-to-engage-politics-in-spires/">Blogging to Engage: Politics in Spires</a>Kate Candy, Department of Politics and International Relations</p>
<p style="padding: 2px 6px 4px 6px;color: #555555;background-color: #eeeeee;border: #dddddd 2px solid"><a title="Documenting Obama’s first 100 days: Student podcasting" href="http://blogs.it.ox.ac.uk/ltg-casestudies/2009/07/29/documenting-obamas-first-100-days-student-podcasting/">Documenting Obama’s first 100 days: Student podcasting</a> Orla De Burca, MSc student reading Global Governance and Diplomacy at St Cross College</p>
							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
